The paper deals with the rank problem in succinct data structures, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and has been extensively studied in the literature. The paper presents a lower bound for the problem in the cell probe model, which is a standard model for studying data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity (FOCS'08), so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC) in the context of the cell probe model. Finally, the paper uses combinatorial arguments (cs.DM) to prove the lower bound.
